{
  "stem": "10698.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Oh, God.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[LAUGHTER]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 101,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 101,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I saw this picture, or-- or whatever you call, during a 1978, '79 when they were showing from Holocaust, a movie on television.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 101,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I saw my mom's-- I recognized my mother there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 101,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I went to New York to find the-- the-- the-- NBC-- NBC borrowed those pictures that the Nazis took.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 101,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and there are three younger women, and the one that is older, you can see.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 101,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It-- she survived with-- she's surrounded-- excuse me-- she's surrounded with dead bodies and soldiers.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 101,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were the next to be exterminated.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] Who knows how long they were schlepping her around?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 103,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When she was taken-- when she was taken away.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 103,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So maybe they got her into the 60s, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 104,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 104,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I don't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 104,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Because you didn't wind up in your own cities, or your own places of birth.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 105,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is my husband and myself, Leo Greenbaum, Helen Greenbaum, and in Berlin, Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 106,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my-- well, figure out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 106,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My-- my-- my son was three-- three months in the tummy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 107,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is my son, Martin Greenbaum, my grandson, Arthur Greenbaum, and my younger grandson, Ian Greenbaurm.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 109,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1987.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 110,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Cali-- what?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 111,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right here.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 112,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right here in Irvine.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 113,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 114,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One is 18, just turned 18.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 114,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And another one is 12.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 114,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And-- and-- and I brought--",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 115,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I brought this one that it survived in Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 115,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I brought this, and that also survived.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 116,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 117,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 118,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my sister and I, Rosalie Wattenberg, and Helen Greenbaum, myself, are showing a table cloth that survived the war in-- in the United States, because my mother used to embroider.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 118,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was her hobby.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 118,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she sent this table cloth to my Aunt, [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 118,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Rae. ?] And there are two initials on it, my-- my mom's initial and my Aunt's [?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 118,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Rea's ?] initial.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 118,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I cherish that table cloth.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 118,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Hopefully, my-- my son will cherish it as much one day when he's going to get it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 119,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He's going to get it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 120,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Somebody made-- this was not a bought drawing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 120,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Somebody did draw the-- my-- my-- about the-- a wish for Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 120,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and they made a herring, and a fish, and a bottle of wine, and a challah and my mom's name, Devora Leah Fromer, embroidered there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 120,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was sent to the United States, also, to my-- to my Aunt [?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 120,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Rae. ?]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 121,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All before the war.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 122,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From Warsaw to New York.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
